\f0\b\fs50 \cf0 Easy Tzatziki with Toasted Pita Crisps\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs30 \cf2 Serves:  
\b0 \cf0 8 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 (7-ounce) containers Greek yogurt (recommended: Fage Total)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 hothouse cucumber, unpeeled and seeded\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup sour cream\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 tablespoons freshly squeezed {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/lemon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 lemon juice}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/vinegar/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 white wine vinegar}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon minced fresh dill\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 1/2 teaspoons minced garlic\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 teaspoons kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper\
{\listtext	\'95	}Toasted Pita Crisps, recipe follows\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs42 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs40 \cf0 Place the yogurt in a medium bowl. Grate the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cucumber/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cucumber}} on a box {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/grater/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 grater}} and squeeze the grated cucumber with your hand to remove some of the liquid. Add it to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/yogurt/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 yogurt}} along with the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/sour-cream/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 sour cream}}, lemon juice, vinegar, dill, garlic, salt and pepper and stir. Serve with toasted pita crisps.\
Toasted Pita Crisps:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}8 pita breads\
{\listtext	\'95	}Good olive oil\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
\cf0 Heat a gas grill or charcoal grill with coals. Brush the pita with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/olive-oil/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 olive oil}} and heat on both sides until toasted.\
Yield: 8 servings\
